4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT LIMITING THE USE OF ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE SYSTEMS
5 BY STATE AND LOCAL GOVERNMENT; PROHIBITING CERTAIN USES OF ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE
6 SYSTEMS; REQUIRING DISCLOSURE OF CERTAIN USES OF ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE SYSTEMS;
7 REQUIRING CERTAIN DECISIONS OR RECOMMENDATIONS TO BE REVIEWED BY A HUMAN IN AN
8 APPROPRIATE RESPONSIBLE POSITION; AND PROVIDING DEFINITIONS.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Definitions. As used in [sections 1 through 4], unless the context clearly
13 indicates otherwise, the following definitions apply:
14 (1) "Artificial intelligence system" means a machine learning-based system that, for any explicit or
15 implicit objective, infers from the inputs the system receives how to generate outputs, including but not limited
16 to content, decisions, predictions, and recommendations that can influence physical or virtual environments.
17 (2) "Government entity" has the meaning provided in 46-5-110.
18 (3) "Human in an appropriate responsible position" means a human person who is a state officer or
19 a public employee as those terms are defined in 2-2-102 who has reasonable training in the uses and
20 limitations of artificial intelligence systems and is in a position to modify or reject the particular use of an artificial
21 intelligence system.
22 (4) "State officer" has the meaning provided in 2-2-102.
23
24 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Prohibited use of artificial intelligence by government entity. A
25 government entity or state officer may not use an artificial intelligence system:
26 (1) for the cognitive behavioral manipulation of a person or group;
27 (2) to classify a person or group based on behavior, socioeconomic status, or personal
28 characteristics resulting in unlawful discrimination or a disparate impact on a person or group based on an
