1 actual or perceived differentiating characteristic;
2 (3) for a deceptive or malicious purpose;
3 (4) for surveillance of public spaces, except:
4 (a) to locate a missing person; or
5 (b) in conformity with Title 44, chapter 15, part 1, regarding continuous facial surveillance.
6
7 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Required disclosures by government entities. (1) If a government
8 entity or state officer publishes material produced by an artificial intelligence system that is not reviewed by a
9 human in an appropriate responsible position, the material must be accompanied by a disclosure that the
10 material was produced by an artificial intelligence system.
11 (2) If a government entity or state officer has an interface with the public that uses an artificial
12 intelligence system, the use of the artificial intelligence system in the interface must be disclosed.
13
14 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Required review. If an artificial intelligence system produces a
15 recommendation or decision for a government entity or state officer that could impact the rights, duties, or
16 privileges and immunities of a person, the recommendation or decision must be reviewed and is subject to
17 rejection or modification by a human in an appropriate responsible position.
18
19 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Codification instruction. [Sections 1 through 4] are intended to be
20 codified as an integral part of Title 2, and the provisions of Title 2 apply to [sections 1 through 4].
21
22 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Severability. If a part of [this act] is invalid, all valid parts that are
23 severable from the invalid part remain in effect. If a part of [this act] is invalid in one or more of its applications,
24 the part remains in effect in all valid applications that are severable from the invalid applications.
